<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911007-0066</DOCNO><DOCID>911007-0066.</DOCID><HL>   Gates Rubber Lawsuit   Accuses Uniroyal Inc.   Of Fraud in Unit Sale</HL><DATE>10/07/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7A</SO><CO>   GR</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)ENVIRONMENT (ENV)LAW AND LEGAL AFFAIRS (LAW)</IN><NS>ENVIRONMENTAL NEWS (ENV)LAW andamp; LEGAL ISSUES AND LEGISLATION (LAW)</NS><RE>COLORADO (CO)CONNECTICUT (CT)NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)SOUTH CAROLINA (SC)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Gates Rubber Co. filed a lawsuit Thursday infederal court in Manhattan against Uniroyal Inc. and itsliquidation trustees alleging that the chemical company,which began liquidating in 1986, committed fraud in sellingone of its units.   Gates Rubber, the largest subsidiary of closely held GatesCorp., Denver, purchased a Uniroyal rubber productssubsidiary for $125 million in 1986. That year Uniroyal,assisted by the investment-banking firm Clayton andamp; DubilierInc., merged its tire unit with B.F. Goodrich and sold offmore than $1 billion of subsidiaries.</LP><TEXT>   Uniroyal chose to liquidate after spending $950 million tofend off a takeover bid by Carl Icahn.   According to the lawsuit, Uniroyal officers knew ofenvironmental hazards at its subsidiary's transmission-beltplant in Monck's Corner, S.C., but did not tell Gates.   Gates now seeks to recover the cleanup costs and punitivedamages from Uniroyal, Uniroyal Holding Co., CDU Holding Co.Inc. and CDU liquidating trust. At the time liquidation beganCDU held almost all of Uniroyal stock. The lawsuit also namesthe four liquidation trustees as defendants.   An attorney for Gates Rubber said the company is still inthe process of calculating how much it has spent on cleaningup the South Carolina site.   Neither Uniroyal, CDU Holding nor the trustees could bereached for comment.   A spokesman for Uniroyal Holding Co., which is based inWaterbury, Conn., along with CDU and the liquidating trust,said he had not seen the suit and could not comment.</TEXT></DOC>